The Shot Path | The SECRET Key to Elite Level Shooting: Basketball Shooting Form FREE Quick Draw Shooting Workout: http://bit.ly/2HgZfQf Follow Us For More B.T.S Content and Exclusive Drills:   / shotmechanics   In today's video, I break down one of the most controversial topics on basketball shooting and that is the "The Shot Path". I give you my thoughts on what is truly the best option when it comes to your own basketball shooting mechanics, and optimizing your own shot path! Here at shotmechanics we think that each individual shooter has unique shooting mechanics so what might work for one player might not always work for another player. Make sure you pay close attention because your shot path is oftentimes a huge issue for a ton of young players! I give you 3 Pro-level shooting tips to help you instantly make more shots while fixing your own shot path. These simple basketball shooting techniques are super easy to implement for players at every level. By implementing these tips into your game you can almost immediately skyrocket your shooting percentage! My first talking point I dive in and explain to you what the S- Curve is when talking about your shot path! The S- Curve is and Elite level shooting secret that most of the great shooters in the NBA have in their basketball shooting form. The S-curve is really just the idea that your shot path creates an S while you bring up your shot. I also give you some examples of the best shooters in the NBA having a great S-Curve guys like Stephen Curry, Damian Lillard and Klay Thompson. The reason for this is because they need a little more force to really shoot with peak fluidity from 3 point range. My second pro tip to help you Master the secret key to elite-level shooting is practicing implementing the S-curve into your slow motion form shooting. By implementing the motion you can really start to master the movement. One thing that I recommend when working on your S-Curve is to take a video of your self shooting to ensure that the shot is coming up straight. By practicing this it will almost immediately help you get the form down with will help you instantly make more shot while keeping your shooting path much straighter! This is something we see a lot of the best shooters in the world implement into their game guys like Stephen Curry and Damian Lillard. If your shot prep is dialed in you will never get your shot blocked. So make sure you are working on your shot preparation if you want to really optimize your basketball shooting mechanics. My last shooting tip to help you instantly make more shots is "Confidence"! Confidence is something we see in ALL of the great shooter's guys like James Harden and Damian Lillard do a great job of trusting their preparation so when they are needed to hit daggers in the game it comes easy to them. The truth of the matter is if you are wanting to become the best possible player you can be you need to put in the work to get to gain the confidence to hit big shots. As I say in the video reps + success = CONFIDENCE. Make sure to implement these pro secrets to lights out shooting into your game today! Want more ShotMechanics?
